{
  "$comment": "AFL Fantasy per-season tier (Premier League / D-League) membership and champions — the single source of truth for the all-play side competition. MFL does NOT store tier membership (its all-play export returns one 24-team list with no tier markers), so it lives here. Keyed by year. `membership` maps franchiseId -> tier as teams competed THAT season; `champions` records the #1 of each tier (slugs premier-league / dleague-champion). Membership for the latest completed season is seeded from afl.config.json; future-year membership and computed champions are written by scripts/compute-afl-tier-movement.mjs (promotion/relegation roll-forward, idempotent). Pre-2025 years carry only hand-entered champions because per-year membership was never recorded and is not recoverable from MFL (see docs/claude/insights/features/afl-trophy-wall.md). 2018-2019 tier champions were never recorded.",
